<section
  id="presentation"
  class="pres-section w-[80%] mx-auto border-l border-r border-b border-white/20"
>
  <div class="pres-inner">
    <!-- Badge + heading -->
    <div class="pres-header">
      <span class="pres-badge">AUTHOR · BACKGROUND</span>
      <h2 class="pres-title">Behind This Analysis</h2>
      <p class="pres-subtitle">
        A mining engineer in training, exploring what data can reveal about the industry.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Two-column body -->
    <div class="pres-grid">
      <!-- Left: who I am -->
      <div class="pres-card">
        <span class="pres-card__label">Who I Am</span>
        <p class="pres-card__text">
          I am a <strong>mining engineering student</strong> who is passionate about understanding the
          technical and territorial realities of extraction. My daily work revolves around geology, mine
          planning, and production — but I believe the best engineers are also the ones who can read and
          communicate data clearly.
        </p>
        <p class="pres-card__text">
          This project is part of the <strong
            ><a href="https://www.codedex.io/community/monthly-challenge/fuyhn9sB6nFKfPKXSvtF"
              >Codedex Challenge February 2026</a
            ></strong
          >, a competition that pushes developers and engineers to build meaningful projects with
          code. For me it was the perfect excuse to apply data analysis to a field I already know
          and care about.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Right: why data science -->
      <div class="pres-card">
        <span class="pres-card__label">Why Data Science × Mining</span>
        <p class="pres-card__text">
          I am not pursuing a career as a data scientist — I am a mining engineer who wants to use <strong
            >data analysis as a professional tool</strong
          >. Knowing how to clean a dataset, identify patterns across hundreds of mine sites, or
          visualize regional distributions gives me a real edge in planning, reporting, and
          decision-making on the field.
        </p>
        <p class="pres-card__text">
          This site is a <strong>data presentation</strong> — not a dashboard. Each section shows the
          results obtained from the analysis: charts, maps, and distributions that make the findings readable
          and meaningful, accompanied by the corresponding interpretation of what the data actually says.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
